[Raza Habib Raja](http://pakteahouse.net/2013/09/07/who-is-a-muslim/) at Pak
Tea House comments:

> The biggest ‘crime’ in Pakistan is to be what I call, Non-Muslim Muslims. So
> if you are an Ahmedi, Shiite, and even a believer in some Sufi Saint you
> will invariably be called Non-Muslim by some.

That brings one to the question “Who is a Muslim?” Raja tells:

> Asking this question is dangerous and trying to define a Muslim is futile
> and would invariably lead to exclusion of many who do not belong to the sect
> of the person who is asking the question.

